g spoken word segments over an ominous orchestral-led instrumental with droning synth. </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="麦莉·赛勒斯（Miley Cyrus） - 前奏（官方视频）" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/sqEWXVn4-VM?feature=oembed&enablejsapi=1" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> “Like when following an image from a train, your eyes can&#39;t keep the passing landscapes from being swallowed into endless distance,” Cyrus says. “Like when holding a fist full of ashes, your hands can&#39;t save the things that have already been dissolved into air.</p><p> “Like when facing the sun through a window, your skin feels warmth but you can&#39;t be in the world that its warmth has made alive. Like walking alone through a lucid dream like saying your name aloud in an empty room.”</p><p> Cyrus co-produced &#39;Prelude&#39; with Everett, Michael Pollack, Jonathan Rado and her boyfriend Maxx Morando.</p><p> The song&#39;s official visuals depict Cyrus in the same outfit as on the &#39;Something Beautiful&#39; artwork – an “archival 1997 Thierry Mugler couture”.</p><p> Before the track hits its cinematic crescendo, an emotional Cyrus stares down the camera lens to state that “the beauty one finds alone is a prayer that longs to be shared”. The video was directed by Cyrus, Bixenman and Walter. Watch above.</p><p> As predicted by some fans, &#39;Prelude&#39; suggests that the singer has moved away from straight-up pop on her new LP in favour of a more experimental – and perhaps darker – sound.</p><p> The &#39;Something Beautiful&#39; film has been called “a one-of-a-kind pop opera from the mind of Miley Cyrus”. The official description reads: “A unique visual experience, fuelled by fantasy, including 13 original songs from the upcoming album.”</p><p> In <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/miley-cyrus-endless-summer-vacation-review-lyrics-tracklist-3409627">a four-star review of &#39;Endless Summer Vacation&#39;</a> , <em>NME</em> wrote: “It all adds up to an album that holds your full attention even if it isn&#39;t Cyrus&#39;s boldest or most visionary. &#39;Endless Summer Vacation&#39; certainly feels like an accurate reflection of who she is as an artist – and a person – in 2023.” </p><div id="adm-inline-article-ad-1" class="admz "><div class="adma boomerang " data-device="Desktop" data-width="300"><div class="pmc-adm-boomerang-pub-div ad-text" data-priority="11"></div></div></div><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/miley-cyrus-shares-dramatic-and-ominous-new-song-prelude-3850678">Listen to Miley Cyrus&#39; dramatic and ominous new song &#39;Prelude&#39;</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
